{
  "stem": "7458.2",
  "chunk_idx": 2,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 3.8,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 6,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "I have a feeling that our family was just too large, the roots were too deep, and breaking away for a part of it to leave Poland was probably a challenge that my father and mother did not want to take.",
      "word_count": 41
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 6,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "They did not want to break up the family.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 6,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 7,
      "text": "How do you pick up eight children with spouses and grandchildren and-- and leave aunts and uncles behind, and so many of them, and just go off to unknown lands?",
      "word_count": 30
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 7,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "But to answer your question, in the 1930s, we began to-- in fact, we-- my father bought a radio.",
      "word_count": 19
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 7,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "And we were one of the first families in town to have a radio.",
      "word_count": 14
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 7,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "And we began to hear a lot of news about the rise of Nazism.",
      "word_count": 14
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 7,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "And-- but people didn't believe everything they heard.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 7,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "Jews-- Jewish people-- have been persecuted for thousands of years.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 7,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "Everywhere we where in many countries we were subjected to antisemitism and to persecution.",
      "word_count": 14
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 7,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "This was nothing new.",
      "word_count": 4
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 8,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "So there is a mad man by the name of Hitler, who is-- who wrote a book, saying that he would annihilate the Jewish people altogether if he had the chance.",
      "word_count": 31
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 8,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "But we-- my parents probably felt, well, that's another Khmelnysky, or another situation like in Spain, or another situation like in many other parts of the world, where we always managed to get by it and to survive and to go on.",
      "word_count": 42
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 9,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "And so they probably denied the seriousness of it, and therefore, did nothing to take steps to get out of Poland when we still could do that.",
      "word_count": 27
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 9,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "Unfortunately, before too long, it was too late.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 9,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "Of course, the Polish government was terribly antisemitic as well.",
      "word_count": 10
    }
  ],
